    <ExplicitInverseRef name="myFileDataStorageHeader" id="4eddbb4d-6c6a-4f42-9473-256b53360e02">
        <kind>parent</kind>
        <transientToPersistentAllowed/>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="CM_FileDataStorageHeader"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>
MES1011  USer-defined reports
The huge string array has a maximum of 0247. Because they can paint anything they like in a JRW design, including strings with no max
length, then we need to err on the side of caution and allow for a line greater than 2047. So we will use this existing data structure of a file
storage header and detail lines. Typically there will only be one detail line unless greater than 500,000 

We will still store the fiel content in the huge string array cuse this is what is displayed on a 'view file' in the Cam Protocl form.
But we write the file for 'transfer' from this ref</text>
        <Inverse name="CM_FileDataStorageHeader::myParent"/>
    </ExplicitInverseRef>
